 Medical innovation has little to do with investment and profit Jonathan Cohn. "Creative Destruction. The best case against universal health care." The New Republic. November 12, 2007 - "[...]The development of DBS was one part basic knowledge--an understanding of how Parkinson's works and how the brain responds to electrical stimulation--and one part sheer luck. Profits, on the other hand, had relatively little to do with it. ."
